Advice. From one of the best to ever do it, @recedavis. 💫🏈

Fun story: in 2001, I spent winter break visiting Bristol, CT. I asked a producer I had met while playing at @pitt_fb if I could get a tour of @espn. He said, “of course.” (Thanks Michael Fountain/Ed Placey!) 

My Dad and I drove up on a snowy day and spent a day and evening watching from the control room. Hosting that day was @recedavis. Alongside was Dr. Lou Holtz and Mark May. 

After the show, I walked on the set and the kindness shown to a 19 year old who was inspired and dreaming of being on a tv set one day was everything one would hope.

From that day on I became a huge @recedavis fan & he has continued to support countless broadcasters with his craft, and advice. Me included. 

Hope everyone in college and all who have started off their careers take a listen/share his wisdom. After all, a rising tide floats all boats. ❤️💫
